<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-02-28T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-02-28T06:00:00-05:00" n="741" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d741">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">761.94/1284: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-02-28T14:00:00+03:00">February 28,
                                1941—2 p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received 3:14 p.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>389. Following has been sent to Tokyo:</p>
                    <p>“I very much appreciate your 321, of February 27, 1 p.m., as I am now
                        convinced that my Japanese colleague has been entirely [accurate?] and
                        sincere during the past 2 or 3 months in his statements to me concerning the
                        status from time to time of the Soviet-Japanese negotiations and that I may
                        in consequence place reliance on any further information that I may obtain
                        from him.[”]</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>